    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      673.42,
      170.59,
      686.38
    ],
    "text": "postponed.",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      727.87,
      521.5,
      756.04
    ],
    "text": "Page 4 of 7",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle",
      "BookmanOldStyle-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      74.64,
      520.35,
      87.6
    ],
    "text": "In view of the above section if the accused has a history of unsound mind the trial",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      98.42,
      520.58,
      111.38
    ],
    "text": "judge has to ascertain that the accused is of good health and is capable of",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      122.3,
      520.15,
      135.26
    ],
    "text": "understanding the charge against him and then act accordingly. But in the instant",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      146.06,
      520.39,
      159.02
    ],
    "text": "matter the trial judge had solely relied on the report of Dr Neil Fernando and has",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      169.82,
      520.1,
      182.78
    ],
    "text": "proceeded to trial without considering the contrary report filed of record at the",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      193.7,
      520.07,
      206.66
    ],
    "text": "non-summary. At this stage the learned Counsel for the respondents submitted",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      217.46,
      520.38,
      230.42
    ],
    "text": "that the report of Dr. Neil Fernando was very comprehensive and that a special",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      241.34,
      520.03,
      254.3
    ],
    "text": "inquiry need not have been held. But we are unable to agree with the same",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      265.13,
      520.19,
      278.09
    ],
    "text": "because the legislature had recommended that the trial judge should go in to the",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      288.89,
      520.6,
      301.85
    ],
    "text": "matter first before proceeding to trial is because it is fundamental in criminal law",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      312.77,
      520.05,
      325.73
    ],
    "text": "that an accused has to be able to understand the offence he is being charged",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      336.53,
      520.1,
      349.49
    ],
    "text": "with and especially when there is contrary view on the matter, the best would",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      360.29,
      520.02,
      373.25
    ],
    "text": "have been to lead evidence and give a chance for the accused to cross examine",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      384.17,
      520.55,
      397.13
    ],
    "text": "the expert who says that he is fit to plead. At this stage both Counsel were unable",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      407.93,
      520.48,
      420.89
    ],
    "text": "to assist court with regard to any decided authority except for an Indian",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      431.71,
      520.16,
      444.67
    ],
    "text": "judgement submitted by the learned counsel for appellant. In the said judgment",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      455.59,
      520.5,
      468.55
    ],
    "text": "the parallel section in the Indian Code of Criminal Procedure Code to section 375",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      479.35,
      520.49,
      492.31
    ],
    "text": "and 374 of our CPC is section 328, and the cited judgment which is the state of",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri",
      "Calibri-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      502.0,
      520.35,
      516.19
    ],
    "text": "Maharastra vs Subasinghe on 20th July 1994 by the Bombay High Court had said",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      8.520000457763672,
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      526.99,
      154.75,
      539.95
    ],
    "text": "as follows,",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri",
      "Calibri-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      562.75,
      520.34,
      575.71
    ],
    "text": "It can be seen that section 328 Cr.P.C. provides that if during an enquiry a",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      586.63,
      520.01,
      599.59
    ],
    "text": "Magistrate has a reason to believe that the accused is of unsound mind he has",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      610.42,
      520.02,
      623.38
    ],
    "text": "to first enquire into this aspect, and if he is convinced about the insanity, he",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      634.18,
      520.46,
      647.14
    ],
    "text": "has to stop the enquiry. Under section 329 Cr.P.C. a trial has to be mandatorily",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      658.06,
      520.1,
      671.02
    ],
    "text": "postponed on finding the accused to be insane. Section 330 Cr.P.C. suggests a",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      681.82,
      520.07,
      694.78
    ],
    "text": "course to be taken for the good care or safe custody of such accused. Section",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      705.58,
      520.59,
      718.54
    ],
    "text": "331 to 333 Cr.P.C. provides that the inquiry or the trial as the case may be can",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      727.87,
      521.5,
      756.04
    ],
    "text": "Page 5 of 7",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle",
      "BookmanOldStyle-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      74.64,
      520.09,
      87.6
    ],
    "text": "resumed only after the accused has fully recovered from insanity. Thus, the law",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      98.42,
      519.98,
      111.38
    ],
    "text": "takes care, and mandates that the accused must be of sane mind when he is",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      122.3,
      520.0,
      135.26
    ],
    "text": "tried. It is cardinal principal of criminal jurisprudence that the accused must",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      146.06,
      431.88,
      159.02
    ],
    "text": "understand the nature of the charge proceeding against him.",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      181.82,
      520.16,
      194.78
    ],
    "text": "Therefore, we are unable to agree with the learned counsel for the respondents",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      205.7,
      520.2,
      218.66
    ],
    "text": "because the legislature had laid down the procedure to be adopted by courts for",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      229.46,
      520.4,
      242.42
    ],
    "text": "a purpose and the courts must follow the same because justice should not only",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      253.37,
      373.8,
      266.33
    ],
    "text": "be done but it should be seemed to be done as well.",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      289.13,
      519.97,
      302.09
    ],
    "text": "The second point raised by the counsel for the appellant is that in the",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      312.89,
      520.15,
      325.85
    ],
    "text": "Magistrates Court the appellant had not been properly committed to stand trial",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      336.77,
      520.29,
      349.73
    ],
    "text": "in the High court as such the indictment filed by the Attorney General is not",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      360.53,
      126.91,
      373.49
    ],
    "text": "valid.",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      396.29,
      520.05,
      409.25
    ],
    "text": "Chapter 15 of the CPC deals with inquiries to be held by the Magistrate, and",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      420.17,
      520.05,
      433.13
    ],
    "text": "under section 146 of the said chapter the charge has to be read over to the",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      443.95,
      520.54,
      456.91
    ],
    "text": "accused and the accused has to understand the charge. But for that purpose to",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      467.71,
      520.1,
      480.67
    ],
    "text": "be achieved the accused has to be of sound mind, but in the instant matter",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      491.59,
      520.28,
      504.55
    ],
    "text": "according to V1 submitted by Dr. Nallhewa the accused had not been of sound",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      515.35,
      520.57,
      528.31
    ],
    "text": "mind to plead. Hence the next step for the Magistrate would have been to act",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      539.23,
      375.6,
      552.19
    ],
    "text": "under section 374 of the CPC which reads as follows,",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      574.99,
      520.01,
      587.95
    ],
    "text": "374 (1) When a Magistrates Court holding an inquiry or a trial has reason to",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      598.78,
      520.03,
      611.74
    ],
    "text": "believe that the accused is of unsound mind and consequently incapable of",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      622.66,
      520.36,
      635.62
    ],
    "text": "making his defense it shall inquire into the fact of such unsoundness and shall",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      646.42,
      520.14,
      659.38
    ],
    "text": "cause such person to be examined by the Government medical officer of the",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      670.18,
      520.18,
      683.14
    ],
    "text": "district or some other medical officer, and thereupon shall examine such officer",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      694.06,
      413.4,
      707.02
    ],
    "text": "as a witness and shall reduce the examination to writing.",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      727.87,
      521.5,
      756.04
    ],
    "text": "Page 6 of 7",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle",
      "BookmanOldStyle-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      74.64,
      520.27,
      87.6
    ],
    "text": "In the instant matter the Magistrate had been in possession of V1 and had taken",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      98.42,
      520.18,
      111.38
    ],
    "text": "steps to write to the Minister of Justice to take appropriate action and thereafter",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      122.3,
      520.11,
      135.26
    ],
    "text": "when the ministry has done so the Magistrate presiding had changed and the",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      146.06,
      520.23,
      159.02
    ],
    "text": "succeeding Magistrate had failed to consider all these steps and instead had",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      169.82,
      520.24,
      182.78
    ],
    "text": "proceeded to have non-summary and had concluded the same and had",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      193.7,
      520.45,
      206.66
    ],
    "text": "committed the accused as well which we consider as a clear violation of",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      217.46,
      520.51,
      230.42
    ],
    "text": "procedure and that type of erroneous procedure only vitiates the committal",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      241.34,
      520.01,
      254.3
    ],
    "text": "which denies the fundamental right of an accused to be able to understand the",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      265.13,
      351.72,
      278.09
    ],
    "text": "charge which is being read over to him by court.",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.960000038146973
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      94.58,
      300.89,
      520.0,
      313.85
    ],
    "text": "Then the next question posed by the counsel for appellant is that in the light of",
    "fonts": [
